==English==

=== Noun ===
'''quodlibetarian''' (or quodlibertarian)
# A pedantic, arguementative, picky person, who gets into huge, deep, angry, heated, downright magniloquent arguements, with anyone and everyone, over the stupidest, most littlest, downright insignificant, minor theoretical subjects, tending to ramble during the discussion, and argueing for the sole sake of being able to argue and hear him- or her- self talk.  For example, a quodlibetarian might dispute the existence of this term, not based on any concern that it does not exist (which is clearly does : [http://www.answers.com/topic/quodlibetarian a] [http://www.islandnet.com/~egbird/dict/q.htm b (alternative spelling)] [http://www.babylon.com/definition/quodlibertarian/English c (alternative spelling)] [http://www.thefreedictionary.com/Quodlibetarian d]), but simply out of a desire to argue over the sheer nature of a language that would have a word that would describe a person who gets into such heated arguements over the littlest points, such as whether or not this word exists.